  clockSprite: {fileID: 21300000, guid: ed4699adc1cf98e4a979beefc0018655, type: 3}
  mainCamera: {fileID: 0}
  dialogueCamera: {fileID: 2994467845004234967}
  greeting: Watch your step, detective. The masonry is still unstable from the aftershocks.
    Make it quick.
  answerOne: Just stabilizing the main arches and clearing debris. Standard post-quake
    cleanup, nothing more.
  answerTwo: Never went near it. Tragic collapse, but that's what happens to old,
    unreinforced brick when the ground shakes.
  evidenceCasebook: Yeah, that's what the rubble looked like when my crew arrived.
    A complete mess.
  evidenceRubbing: I'm a mason, not a historian. I don't have time to read old plaques.
  evidenceClock: Wait... is that a freshly cut brass gear? Look, fine! I was up there
    trying to salvage some valuable scrap before the tower came down. But I didn't
    cause the collapse, I swear!
